# Next.js Data Fetching

## Decision Tree

- **Reading data from a Server Component?** Fetch directly (no API layer needed).
- **Mutation from UI (create, update, delete)?** Use a Server Action in `_services/`.
- **External API for webhooks or third-party consumers?** Use a Route Handler (`route.ts`).

## Server Components for Reads

Fetch data directly in Server Components. No API round-trip needed:

```tsx
export const InstructorPage = async ({ params }: Props) => {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const instructor = await fetchInstructor(slug);

  if (!instructor) {
    notFound();
  }

  return <InstructorProfile data={instructor} />;
};

export default InstructorPage;
```

## Server Actions for Mutations

Place mutations in `_services/` files with `'use server'`:

```ts
'use server';

import { createChildLogger } from '@/libs/logger';

export const updateInstructor = async (data: UpdateInstructorInput) => {
  const logger = createChildLogger({ trace: 'updateInstructor' });
  // mutation logic
};
```

## Avoid Data Waterfalls

### Parallel fetching with Promise.all

```tsx
const [instructor, courses, reviews] = await Promise.all([
  fetchInstructor(id),
  fetchCourses(id),
  fetchReviews(id),
]);
```

### Streaming with Suspense

```tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react';

export const InstructorPage = async () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <Suspense fallback={<ProfileSkeleton />}>
        <InstructorProfile />
      </Suspense>
      <Suspense fallback={<CoursesSkeleton />}>
        <CourseList />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  );
};

export default InstructorPage;
```

## Pass Server Data via Props

Pass data from Server Components to Client Components via props. Do not re-fetch on the client what the server already has:

```tsx
// page.tsx (Server Component)
const settings = await fetchSettings();
return <SettingsForm defaultValues={settings} />;
```

## Route Handlers

Use Route Handlers (`route.ts`) only when you need:

- External API access (webhooks from Stripe, third-party integrations)
- HTTP caching semantics (GET endpoints)
- REST API for external consumers
- Cron-triggered endpoints (e.g., Vercel Cron)

Do not use Route Handlers for internal data fetching or UI mutations.

### API Handler Pattern (backend services)

API-only projects (payments-service, email-service) wrap Route Handlers with an `apiHandler` utility from `@/libs/api`:

```ts
import { apiHandler } from '@/libs/api';

export const POST = apiHandler(async (req) => {
  // apiHandler initializes logger, handles errors, returns proper status codes
});
```

For Stripe webhooks, validate the signature before processing:

```ts
const body = await req.text();
const signature = req.headers.get('stripe-signature');
const event = stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(body, signature, STRIPE_CONFIG.WEBHOOK_SECRET);
```
